<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN224-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. cōḻaṉ karikāṟperuvaḷattāṉaik karuṅkuḻalātaṉār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN224">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>aruppam pēṇā tamarkaṭan tatūun</l>
<l>tuṇaipuṇa rāyamoṭu tacumpuṭaṉ ṟolaicci</l>
<l>yirumpā ṇokkaṟ kaṭumpupuran tatūu</l>
<l>maṟamaṟak kaṇṭa neṟimā ṇavaiyattu</l>
<l>muṟainaṟ kaṟiyunar muṉṉuṟap pukaḻnta</l>
<l>tūviyaṟ koḷkait tukaḷaṟu makaḷiroṭu</l>
<l>pariti yuruviṟ palpaṭaip puricai</l>
<l>yeruvai nukarcci yūpa neṭuntūṇ</l>
<l>vēta vēḷvit toḻiṉmuṭit tatūu</l>
<l>maṟintōṉ maṉṟa vaṟivuṭai yāḷa</l>
<l>ṉiṟantōṉ ṟāṉē yaḷittiv vulaka</l>
<l>maruvi māṟi yañcuvarak kaṭukip</l>
<l>peruvaṟaṅ kūrnta vēṉiṟ kālaip</l>
<l>pacitta vāyattup payaṉirai tarumār</l>
<l>pūvāṭ kōvalar pūvuṭa ṉutirak</l>
<l>koytukaṭ ṭaḻitta vēṅkaiyiṉ</l>
<l>melliyaṉ makaḷiru miḻaikaḷain taṉarē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="10ab">He was one indeed who knew </l>
<l corresp="1">of winning battles, not heeding fortresses, </l>
<l corresp="2">of destroying pots together with the united group of companions, </l>
<l corresp="3">[and] protecting the relatives of large bardic kinfolk, </l>
<l corresp="9">and of completing the work of Vedic sacrifices </l>
<l corresp="8">with the large posts of sacrificial poles, to the enjoyment of the kites, </l>
<l corresp="7">in fortifications with many armies of circle-shape, </l>
<l corresp="6">along with speckless women of pure-natured priciples </l>
<l corresp="5">who are praised, while having in front those who well know the ways </l>
<l corresp="4">of the assembly glorious for [its] path that fully saw dharma, </l>
<l corresp="10cd">	the knowledgeable man. </l>
<l corresp="11">He now is one who passed away. Pitiable is the world. </l>
<l corresp="16">Like kino trees, [their] loads destroyed by plucking, </l>
<l corresp="15">while the flowers all drop off on account of the cowherds with flower sickles, </l>
<l corresp="14">in order to give [food] to the yielding rows of the famished herd, </l>
<l corresp="13">in summer time that abounds in big droughts, </l>
<l corresp="12">frighteningly coming near, as the waterfalls change, </l>
<l corresp="17">soft-natured women [now] removed [their] jewels. </l>
</lg>
